  Stokes's theorem in part (a) too. First, we find
  <md>
  <mrow>
  \vnabla\times\vF
  &amp;=\det\left[\begin{matrix}
  \vi &amp;\vj &amp;\vk
  </mrow><mrow>
  \tfrac{\partial }{\partial x} &amp; \tfrac{\partial }{\partial y} &amp;
                  \tfrac{\partial }{\partial z}
  </mrow><mrow>
  z^2 &amp; x^2 &amp; y^2
